  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "An antihelminthic and immunomodulator that has been withdrawn from the U.S. and Canadian markets, due to the risk of serious side effects\nIncreasingly used as a cutting agent in cocaine sold around the globe\n69% of DEA seized cocaine contained levamisole (2009)\n[1]\nResults in Levamisole induced necrosis syndrome\n[2]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Agranulocytosis/Thrombocytopenia\nTypically neutropenia\nTends to reverse spontaneously when discontinued\nLevamisole induced necrosis syndrome\nNecrotic patches anywhere on skin (especially ears and legs)\nLeukoencephalopathy\nSeen when used as a pharmaceutical in past\nNo cases described when associated with cocaine adulteration",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
